{{wikipedia}}
==English==

===Etymology===
Named after the Italian scientist B. Eustachio

===Noun===
'''[[Eustachian]] [[tube]]''' 
# {{anatomy}} In [[human]]s and other land [[vertebrate]]s, a tube that links the [[pharynx]] to the cavity of the [[middle ear]] to allow the [[equilization]] of the [[pressure]] on both sides of the [[eardrum]].

